reviewText: This was a nice change of pace.  We usually buy the baby einstein movies, but my son was so into animals I bought this.  He loved it.  He just laughs and names all of the animals and foods.  I would say this movie can be watched by kids older than 18 months.
Title: N/A

reviewerName: Karen B - mom of 5, including triplets!
reviewText: My triplets are now 15 months old and they LOVE this DVD. They started out watching Baby Einstein which they loved, but Curious Buddies has a more bouncy and funky fun music that they love to dance and bounce to and fun songs to sing along with. They learn stuff too.
Title: N/A

reviewText: My 2 year old can't get enough Curious Buddies! I had a large collection of the dvds years ago but got rid of them when my daughter out grew them. But then came another baby so I bought them all again. They are very interactive and keep them engaged. My 2 year old loves to sing and dance along

reviewText: I couldn't really tell you why my 2 year old grand daughter loves these Curious Buddies videos. I think she just loves the little ones that are like her. I saw an advertisement on another video for Curious Buddies and just had to order her one. She loves it and watches it over and over again.
